article.headline: Stony Brook 56, UMBC 55
article.story: STONYBROOK, N.Y. -- Chris Martin made a free throw with 18 seconds left to give Stony Brook a 56-55 victory against Maryland-Baltimore County on Saturday night. Matt Spadafora made a 3-pointer with 46 second left to tie the game at at 55 for UMBC (9-12, 3-6 America East). Muhammad El-Amin led the Seawolves (12-10, 4-5) with 15 points and Martin added 11. Darryl Proctor led the Retrievers with a game-high 20 points. Spadafora scored 11 points and Justin Fry added 10 points and 12 rebounds . Stony Brook led 27-25 at half and never trailed, though the game was tied eight times.
